<TEXT>
<P>
Hail, Carmen: Actress Carmen Zapata, co-founder and president of Los Angeles' 
Bilingual Foundation of the Arts, has been awarded the Civil Order of Merit by 
His Majesty Juan Carlos I, King of Spain. The order of knighthood, which 
recognizes Zapata's commitment to arts in the Hispanic community, was 
originally instituted by royal decree on June 25, 1926. GREG BRAXTON 
