<P>
SECURITY FORCE TO MERGE WITH 2 UNITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parliament voted to merge Iran's internal security force, the Islamic 
Revolutionary Komitehs, with other urban and paramilitary rural police to 
battle an insurgency and drug-trafficking in the border area with Pakistan. The 
action was opposed by some conservative members who said it was designed to 
dissolve the Komitehs, created after the 1979 revolution partly to safeguard 
the government against counterrevolutionary elements. 
</P>
