<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIT-AND-RUN ACCIDENTS SOAR TO RECORD LEVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JESSE KATZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kenny Ly, a cherubic 4-year-old who could count to 100 and recite his ABCs, 
never saw the speeding blue-green sedan as he stepped off the curb last April 
onto a quiet San Gabriel side street. 
</P>
<P>
The front bumper of the car ripped Kenny from his mother's hand, and hurled him 
68 feet. The driver sped off, leaving behind only a shattered headlight and a 
few specks of paint embedded in the boy's jeans. Kenny was dead. 
</P>
<P>
Since then, detectives have spent dozens of hours staking out the crime scene, 
searching the neighborhood and even debating whether hypnosis might help 
Kenny's parents recall more about the accident. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Full Run; Infobox; List 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
HIT AND RUN DRIVERS; TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- CALIFORNIA; CRIME STATISTICS; LAW 
ENFORCEMENT; POLICE INVESTIGATIONS; TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; 
AUTOMOBILE SAFETY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061190-0089 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 232144 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 11, 1990, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
107 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIG SPENDERS: Sure, they love to eat out in the Bay Area (above), but when it 
comes to dining in Southern California, no one spends like people do in Orange 
County. . . . The average local household spent nearly $3,000 a year in 
restaurants and bars in 1988. That's about $730 more than in San Diego County, 
about $830 more than in Los Angeles County and a whopping $1,325 more than in 
Riverside County. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
EATING OUT IN CALIFORNIA 
</P>
<P>
Most spent per household in bars and restaurants, by county. 
</P>
<P>
San Francisco: $4,426 
</P>
<P>
Orange: $2,966 
</P>
<P>
Marin: $2,726 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara: $2,640 
</P>
<P>
Placer: $2,484 
</P>
<P>
