<P>
1 KILLED, 2ND HURT AS PICKUP OVERTURNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was killed and another injured when their pickup truck spun out of 
control and overturned on a freeway transition ramp early Sunday, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Gabriel Frausto Jr., 24, of Placentia was pronounced dead at the scene of the 
4:05 a.m. accident on the transition ramp between the eastbound Riverside and 
northbound Orange freeways, according to the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Frank Estrada, 25, of Anaheim, believed to have been a passenger in the silver 
1988 Toyota truck, was being treated for moderate injuries at Western Medical 
Center in Santa Ana, CHP officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver was believed to have been too drunk to negotiate the curving ramp 
and instead lost control of the truck, which spun around and overturned several 
times, a patrol spokesman said. Both men were thrown from the truck. Neither 
was wearing a seat belt. 
</P>
