<P>
SKATEBOARDER DIES OF HEAD INJURIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old skateboarder has died of injuries sustained last week when he 
fell off his skateboard while hanging onto the back of a moving car and crushed 
his skull on a shopping center driveway, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Joel Christopher Banks, a student at Saddleback College, was pronounced dead 
about 1:30 a.m. Saturday, said a spokeswoman at Mission Hospital Regional 
Medical Center in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday night, Banks and Graeme E. Swayn, a roommate, held onto the back 
of their friend's Toyota Celica while the car towed them up a steep driveway 
leading out of the Monarch Bay Plaza shopping center. Banks' skateboard caught 
a patch of rough concrete, and he was knocked backward onto the ground. Swayn 
was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
Banks, who was not wearing a helmet, crushed his skull and slipped into a coma. 
</P>
<P>
Banks moved from Dublin, a Bay Area town near Oakland, two years ago. 
</P>
