<P>
MAN SHOT NEAR VAN NUYS AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An argument over a minor traffic accident in the parking lot of a restaurant 
near Van Nuys Airport escalated into a shooting this morning that left one man 
injured. Los Angeles police were seeking the suspected gunman, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Kenny Kingsberry, 28, of Los Angeles was shot twice in the stomach and taken to 
an undisclosed hospital where he was in serious but stable condition, Sgt. 
Dallas Gibson said. An unidentified man is being sought in the 2 a.m. shooting 
in the parking lot of the 94th Aero Squadron restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred as the restaurant was closing and the two men's cars 
apparently were involved in a minor accident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a dispute over a traffic accident and, while they were arguing, shots 
were fired," Gibson said. 
</P>
<P>
The shooter fled in his car. Though several patrons were leaving the restaurant 
at the time, no one could provide police with a description of the gunman or 
his car. 
</P>
