<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
GUNFIRE HITS TRUCK, NARROWLY MISSES DRIVER ON O.C. FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pickup truck traveling on the Costa Mesa Freeway early today was riddled with 
gunfire from another vehicle for no apparent reason, California Highway Patrol 
officials reported. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck, Sinarta Bangun, 28, of Anaheim was not injured in the 
2:15 a.m. attack on the southbound Costa Mesa Freeway just north of the Garden 
Grove Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
Bangun's truck was struck five times, with three bullets striking the rear 
tailgate, another bullet hitting the right side of the cab and the fifth round 
slamming through the rear window, missing the driver by about an inch, CHP 
spokeswoman Angel Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
Bangun was unable to provide officers with a description of the vehicle, nor an 
explanation on why the shooting might have happened. Angel said Bangun told 
police only that the rifle shots were fired from a vehicle behind him and that 
"he couldn't see anything." 
</P>
<P>
The case has been turned over to the Orange County Sheriff's Department for 
investigation. 
</P>
