WEMBLEY INDOOR MATCH DROPPED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEMBLEY, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The men's indoor tennis tournament held here each autumn for the last 14 years 
was dropped today when its chief sponsor pulled out, citing "changes in the 
men's professional tour." 
</P>
<P>
Promoters said they had considered all alternatives and "regrettably, there is 
no other acceptable course available to us." 
</P>
<P>
The tournament, first known as the Benson and Hedges Championships, was to have 
been staged Nov. 5-11. But tournament director Len Owen said the sponsors were 
concerned that, with that week designated as a "free week" by the Assn. of 
Tennis Professionals, "we faced the threat of exhibition matches featuring top 
players being staged against us." 
